{"actual_usd":0.12464,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":212,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24292,"reply":"\"No.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron and glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"If he's only an example, then his death is mostly a tragic flourish at the end of a good lesson. Sad, maybe stirring—but not necessary.\"\n\n*I lean my forearms on the table a little.* \"But the trouble with us isn't just that we need better instruction. We need forgiveness. We need rescue. A drowning man does not mainly need someone on the shore demonstrating the right stroke. He needs a hand that can actually pull him out. That's why the cross matters. Not just, 'look how much love this is,' but 'something happened here for us that we could not do for ourselves.'\"\n\n\"I think that's the place where the whole thing stands or falls, Ryan. If Jesus only shows the way, then we're still left carrying our guilt with improved manners. If he dies to bear sin and reconcile us to God—ah. That's different. That's salvation.\"","rolling_24h_usd":45.04596500000004,"run_id":"ce0d0878-17b3-4f48-949f-2a7f66a09ca5"}
